name: informed consent form
definition: A document that explains all relevant information to assist a human being in understanding the expectations and requirements of participation in a process, and is an instrument in obtaining consent and, after having obtained consent, is a record that such a consent has occurred.

name: informed consent form containing questionnaire
definition: An informed consent form that contains a questionnaire section.

name: informed consent form for clinical research involving children
definition: An informed consent form for clinical study that involves children.

name: informed consent form for clinical study
definition: An informed consent form that is used for a clinical study.

name: informed consent form for genetic study
definition: An informed consent form that is designed for use in genetic studies.

name: informed consent form for human biospecimen collection
definition: An informed consent form that documents a voluntary decision to deposit a human biospecimen.

name: informed consent form for human blood sample collection
definition: An informed consent form that is specifically for human blood sample collection.

name: informed consent form for human saliva sample collection
definition: An informed consent form for human sample collection that is specifically for human saliva sample collection.

name: informed consent form for human urine biospecimen collection
definition: An informed consent form designed for use in human urine collection.

name: informed consent form for qualitative research involving children
definition: An informed consent form for qualitative study that involves children.

name: informed consent form for qualitative study
definition: An informed consent form that is used for a qualitative study.

name: informed consent form for storage and future use of unused samples
definition: An informed consent form that is used for a storage and future use of unused samples.

name: informed consent form for vaccination
definition: An informed consent form that contains sections specific to procedures in vaccination.

name: Clinical Trial Subject Information Form
definition: Documentation given to a subject to provide instructions or information related to the trial.
